cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a deep learning approach for the segmentation of bladder walls and tumor regions in MRI scans of patients with bladder cancer. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG), with a focus on medical image analysis. The use of dilated convolutions and progressive dilations in the proposed network suggests a strong emphasis on neural network architecture design and optimization, which could also place the paper in the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the application of the proposed method to medical imaging data could also make it relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
